1
00:00:19,105 --> 00:00:23,466
孩子们  都坐得舒服吗?
Now, children, are you sitting comfortably?

2
00:00:23,510 --> 00:00:24,841
我开始了
Then I'll begin.

3
00:00:26,880 --> 00:00:30,007
故事始于几千年前
This story started many thousands of years ago,

4
00:00:30,083 --> 00:00:33,177
但只历时了七天
but it was all over in just seven days.

5
00:00:33,253 --> 00:00:35,187
在那个远古时代
All that long, long time ago,

6
00:00:35,222 --> 00:00:37,247
我们现在熟悉的
none of the things we can see now,

7
00:00:37,324 --> 00:00:40,691
太阳  月亮  星星  地球
the sun, the moon, the stars, the earth,

8
00:00:40,727 --> 00:00:44,229
动物和植物  全部都不存在
the animals and plants not a single one existed.

9
00:00:44,329 --> 00:00:46,265
只有上帝存在
Only God existed,

10
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,932
他是唯一的创造者
and so only He could have created them.

11
00:00:48,969 --> 00:00:50,296
他创造了一切
And He did.

12
00:00:51,264 --> 00:00:55,991
小 岛 惊 魂

13
00:02:13,264 --> 00:02:16,791
"泽西岛  海峡群岛"  "1945年"

14
00:03:00,467 --> 00:03:03,702
辛普森  真是大好人
Simpson. What a character he was.

15
00:03:03,737 --> 00:03:05,732
现在不知怎么样了?
I wonder whatever became of him?

16
00:03:05,772 --> 00:03:08,206
大概和其他人一样死了
Oh, I imagine he's dead like all the rest.

17
00:03:08,241 --> 00:03:11,103
当时真是好时光
Ah, those were the days.

18
00:03:20,287 --> 00:03:22,578
特德先生  注意你的头发
Mr. Tuttle, your hair.

19
00:03:30,117 --> 00:03:31,228
什么事?
Yes?

20
00:03:31,325 --> 00:03:34,834
早安  太太  我们是...
Good morning, ma'am. We've come about the...

21
00:03:34,868 --> 00:03:36,463
哦  当然
Oh, yes, of course.

22
00:03:38,505 --> 00:03:39,767
进来
Come in.

23
00:03:41,408 --> 00:03:43,672
想不到这么快就到了
I wasn't expecting you so soon.

24
00:03:51,551 --> 00:03:52,882
你们是?
You are?

25
00:03:52,953 --> 00:03:54,648
我是贝莎米尔丝  太太
I'm Bertha Mills, ma'am.

26
00:03:54,721 --> 00:03:56,814
这位是艾德蒙・特德
And this is Edmund Tuttle.

27
00:03:56,890 --> 00:03:58,482
幸会  太太
Pleased to meet you, ma'am.

28
00:03:58,558 --> 00:04:00,321
你一定是花匠了
You must be the gardener.

29
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:02,624
没错  是花匠
That's right. The gardener.

30
00:04:02,662 --> 00:04:06,655
这位姑娘叫丽蒂亚
And this young lady is called Lydia.

31
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:09,191
你有帮佣的工作经验吗?
Have you had much experience in service?

32
00:04:09,236 --> 00:04:12,603
别被她的娃娃脸骗了  太太
Oh, don't let that angel face fool you, ma'am.

33
00:04:12,639 --> 00:04:14,504
其实她年纪不轻
She's older than she looks.

34
00:04:14,541 --> 00:04:16,441
会烫衣服吗?
Can you iron?

35
00:04:18,678 --> 00:04:20,839
怎么了?  哑巴了?
What's the matter? Has the cat got your tongue?

36
00:04:22,281 --> 00:04:24,515
她不会说话  太太
She can't talk, ma'am.

37
00:04:25,285 --> 00:04:26,843
这个可怜的小姑娘是个哑巴
The poor little mite's a mute.

38
00:04:26,920 --> 00:04:28,221
噢
Oh.

39
00:04:28,221 --> 00:04:29,923
但手脚很灵活
Oh, but she's a good little worker.

40
00:04:29,923 --> 00:04:31,247
这点我可以保证
I can promise you that.

41
00:04:32,024 --> 00:04:33,952
好吧
All right.

42
00:04:33,994 --> 00:04:36,622
从前那个姑娘太笨拙了
All right. The other girl I had spoke too much, anyway.

43
00:04:36,663 --> 00:04:37,328
跟我来
Follow me.

44
00:04:37,364 --> 00:04:38,758
米尔丝太太  你和姑娘的房间
Mrs. Mills, you and the girl

45
00:04:38,758 --> 00:04:41,763
在顶楼
will sleep in the attic room at the top of the stairs.

46
00:04:42,102 --> 00:04:45,560
-而你  -特德 太太
-And you, Mr.  -Tuttle, ma'am.

47
00:04:46,305 --> 00:04:50,042
你可以睡在后面的库房
You could sleep in the shed around the back.

48
00:04:50,376 --> 00:04:53,212
佣人们一周前失踪后
As you can see, the housework has been rather neglected

49
00:04:53,212 --> 00:04:55,878
从那时起就没人打扫过
since the servants disappeared almost a week ago.

50
00:04:55,916 --> 00:04:58,077
他们都不辞而别?
You mean they just vanished?

51
00:04:58,151 --> 00:04:59,881
都蒸发了
Into thin air.

52
00:05:00,354 --> 00:05:01,321
一声不响
No notice, nothing.

53
00:05:01,321 --> 00:05:03,417
甚至连工资都没拿
They didn't even collect their wages. They...

54
00:05:04,256 --> 00:05:06,157
都消失了
They just left us.

55
00:05:06,192 --> 00:05:08,212
真奇怪!
What a strange thing to do.

56
00:05:08,461 --> 00:05:10,363
你们不久就会发现
You'll soon find out there are times

57
00:05:10,363 --> 00:05:13,021
这间屋子不是十全十美
when this house is not exactly an ideal home.

58
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:15,596
所以我在广告声明
Hence my advertisement in the newspaper

59
00:05:15,596 --> 00:05:19,271
要老实  勤劳的人
requesting honest, hardworking people.

60
00:05:19,306 --> 00:05:22,036
谁也不及我们老实  勤劳
There's nobody more honest or hardworking than us.

61
00:05:22,075 --> 00:05:23,474
对吧  特德先生
Isn't that right, Mr. Tuttle?

62
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:25,637
我们是老实人
Oh, aye, we're very honest.

63
00:05:25,679 --> 00:05:28,807
而且很勤劳
And, um, very hardworking.

64
00:05:31,751 --> 00:05:34,083
这是厨房
The kitchen.

65
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:36,020
我八点用早餐
I have breakfast at 8:00

66
00:05:36,056 --> 00:05:38,047
孩子们九点
the children at 9:00.

67
00:05:38,124 --> 00:05:41,389
午餐一点  晚餐七点半
Lunch will be served at 1:00 and dinner at 7:30.

68
00:05:41,428 --> 00:05:43,726
男主人呢  太太?
And the master, ma'am?

69
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:48,824
男主人一年半前
The master went off to war

70
00:05:48,868 --> 00:05:50,699
去战场了
a year and a half ago.

71
00:05:50,737 --> 00:05:53,730
停战后杳无音信
I've had no news since the war ended.

72
00:05:54,774 --> 00:05:56,241
谁负责煮食?
Which of you does the cooking?

73
00:05:56,276 --> 00:05:58,676
真遗憾  太太
I'm so sorry, ma'am

74
00:05:58,712 --> 00:06:00,737
谁负责煮食?
Which of you does the cooking?

75
00:06:00,780 --> 00:06:02,680
看到我做什么吗
You'll notice what I'm doing.

76
00:06:02,716 --> 00:06:06,043
这间屋子关了门
In this house, no door must be opened

77
00:06:06,043 --> 00:06:08,480
才可以开另一扇门
without the previous one being closed first.

78
00:06:08,555 --> 00:06:11,115
一定要紧记
It is vital that you remember this.

79
00:06:11,191 --> 00:06:13,182
实行起来不简单
It's not as easy as it may seem.

80
00:06:13,259 --> 00:06:16,387
十五把锁匙开启五十扇门
There are 15 different keys for all of the 50 doors

81
00:06:16,429 --> 00:06:18,730
要看你们在屋子的哪个地方
depending on which area of the house you're in at the time.

82
00:06:19,866 --> 00:06:22,260
米尔丝太太  明天开始
Mrs. Mills, from tomorrow onwards

83
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:24,970
我会交一套钥匙给你负责
I will be leaving a set of keys in your charge.

84
00:06:25,005 --> 00:06:26,529
好的  太太
Yes, ma'am.

85
00:06:26,773 --> 00:06:28,341
音乐室
The music room.

86
00:06:28,341 --> 00:06:30,444
我们搬来已有的那架老钢琴
That old piano was already here when we moved in.

87
00:06:30,444 --> 00:06:34,074
不要让孩子们乱弹
Please do not let the children thump away on it.

88
00:06:34,615 --> 00:06:36,778
我听了会头痛
It sets off my migraine.

89
00:06:36,816 --> 00:06:38,716
安静
Silence is something that we prize

90
00:06:38,785 --> 00:06:40,515
比什么都重要
very highly in this house.

91
00:06:41,388 --> 00:06:43,822
屋子里没有电话  收音机
That is why you will not find a telephone, a radio

92
00:06:43,822 --> 00:06:45,957
也没有任何弄出响声的东西
or anything else that makes a racket.

93
00:06:46,393 --> 00:06:48,752
我们也没有电
Oh, we don't have electricity, either.

94
00:06:48,795 --> 00:06:50,861
战争时  德国人不断切电
During the war, the Germans kept cutting it off

95
00:06:50,861 --> 00:06:53,798
所以已经习惯了  我们继续生活在不用电的日子里
so we learned to live without it. Let's continue.

96
00:06:53,798 --> 00:06:56,466
太太  其实没必要看整间屋子
Ma'am, there's no need to show us the whole house.

97
00:06:56,503 --> 00:06:57,629
有!
Yes!

98
00:06:57,870 --> 00:07:00,030
有必要
Yes, there is.

99
00:07:00,774 --> 00:07:02,843
屋内经常漆黑一片不见五指
Most of the time, you can hardly see your way.

100
00:07:02,843 --> 00:07:04,545
很难看清
It's often difficuIt to make out

101
00:07:04,545 --> 00:07:08,006
有桌子椅子门餐柜
if there is a table, a chair, a door, a sideboard

102
00:07:09,082 --> 00:07:12,674
或是孩子们在玩捉迷藏游戏
or one of my children playing hide and seek.

103
00:07:12,752 --> 00:07:15,012
这话怎么说?
What do you mean, ma'am?

104
00:07:15,889 --> 00:07:18,915
是时候见见我的孩子了
Perhaps I should introduce you to the children.

105
00:07:24,731 --> 00:07:26,892
特德先生  请你现在去花园
Mr. Tuttle, you can see to the garden now.

106
00:07:26,933 --> 00:07:28,161
工具在库房里
You'll find tooIs in the shed.

107
00:07:28,201 --> 00:07:29,828
是的  太太
Yes, ma'am.

108
00:07:29,869 --> 00:07:32,497
你们两个拉上窗帘
You two can start closing the curtains.

109
00:07:32,539 --> 00:07:34,131
全部窗帘
All of them.

110
00:08:04,204 --> 00:08:06,001
来吧
Come.

111
00:08:16,749 --> 00:08:18,685
我去叫醒他们  你们稍候
I'll wake them. You wait here.

112
00:08:20,220 --> 00:08:22,415
千万别拉开窗帘
Whatever you do, don't open the curtains.

113
00:08:25,792 --> 00:08:28,090
醒醒  醒醒
Wakey, wakey.

114
00:08:30,330 --> 00:08:32,525
快醒醒
Now, come on.

115
00:08:32,565 --> 00:08:35,398
合起眼  合起手
Eyes closed, hands together.

116
00:08:35,435 --> 00:08:38,071
祈福日伊始
Let it be, at light of day

117
00:08:38,071 --> 00:08:40,535
祷告主耶稣
Jesus, to whom now I pray.

118
00:08:40,573 --> 00:08:43,139
祈福玛丽亚
Blessed be the Virgin pure

119
00:08:43,176 --> 00:08:44,969
洁净如朝露
whom I greet with faith too short.

120
00:08:44,969 --> 00:08:47,306
耶稣与玛丽  无瑕圣玫瑰
Jesus, Mary, spotless rose.

121
00:08:47,306 --> 00:08:50,778
愿主保佑我  直至夕阳红
Keep us till this day doth close.

122
00:08:55,989 --> 00:08:58,389
他们还未完全醒
They're still half asleep.

123
00:08:58,424 --> 00:09:01,882
多可爱的孩子
What sweet little children.

124
00:09:01,961 --> 00:09:05,294
应该说些什么呀?
Well what do you say?

125
00:09:05,331 --> 00:09:07,390
你好吗?
How do you do?

126
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:09,333
你好吗?
How do you do?

127
00:09:09,369 --> 00:09:12,805
你们好吗? 孩子们
How do you do, children?

128
00:09:12,839 --> 00:09:14,602
我是米尔丝太太
My name is Mrs. Mills

129
00:09:14,641 --> 00:09:17,872
不过也可以叫我贝莎
but you can call me Bertha if you like.

130
00:09:17,911 --> 00:09:19,742
你们叫什么?
What are your names?

131
00:09:19,779 --> 00:09:21,741
-安  -尼古拉斯
-Anne.  -Nicholas.

132
00:09:21,741 --> 00:09:26,942
安和尼古拉斯  真是好听的名字
Anne and Nicholas. What pretty names.

133
00:09:26,986 --> 00:09:29,819
你是新保姆?
Are you going to be our new nanny?

134
00:09:32,926 --> 00:09:36,327
是的亲爱的  我是你们的新保姆
Yes, my dears. I'm your new nanny.

135
00:09:36,362 --> 00:09:37,693
该吃早餐了
It's time for their breakfast.

136
00:09:37,693 --> 00:09:40,358
丽蒂亚  去关上厨房的窗
Lydia, go to the kitchen and close every shutter.

137
00:09:47,273 --> 00:09:50,106
医生找不到根治方法
The doctors were never able to find a cure.

138
00:09:50,143 --> 00:09:52,111
治什么?
For what?

139
00:09:52,145 --> 00:09:54,579
他们的病情
Their condition.

140
00:09:54,614 --> 00:09:57,851
孩子们对光非常敏感
The children have a very serious allergy to light.

141
00:09:59,085 --> 00:10:01,117
他们绝不能暴露在
They are photosensitive and must never be exposed

142
00:10:01,117 --> 00:10:03,854
比现在强烈的光线之下
to any light much stronger than this.

143
00:10:03,890 --> 00:10:06,154
否则他们即刻
Otherwise, in a matter of minutes

144
00:10:06,192 --> 00:10:08,023
就会出现疱疹  呼吸困难
they will break out in sores and blisters

145
00:10:08,061 --> 00:10:11,326
然后会开始窒息
and begin to suffocate.

146
00:10:11,364 --> 00:10:12,922
严重的话会致命
It would eventually be fatal.

147
00:10:12,966 --> 00:10:15,230
我的天
Good heavens.

148
00:10:16,302 --> 00:10:17,997
我不喜欢这种土司
I don't like this toast.

149
00:10:18,037 --> 00:10:19,664
哦?  为什么?
Oh? Why not?

150
00:10:19,706 --> 00:10:21,867
味道怪怪的
It tastes funny.

151
00:10:21,908 --> 00:10:23,876
从前的较好吃
I liked it better before.

152
00:10:23,910 --> 00:10:28,279
因为从前是别人做的
That's because before, somebody else made it.

153
00:10:28,314 --> 00:10:30,612
他们几时回来?
When are they coming back?

154
00:10:32,619 --> 00:10:34,109
他们不会回来了  孩子们
They're not coming back, child.

155
00:10:34,187 --> 00:10:37,156
和爸爸一样
Just like Daddy.

156
00:10:37,190 --> 00:10:39,658
爸爸会回来的
Daddy is coming back, though.

157
00:10:39,726 --> 00:10:43,856
米尔丝太太  爸爸去法国打仗
Mrs. Mills, our father's fighting in a war in France.

158
00:10:43,896 --> 00:10:45,227
是世界大战
It's the World War.

159
00:10:45,265 --> 00:10:46,933
我知道  但他在法国
I know, but he's in France.

160
00:10:46,967 --> 00:10:48,634
说够了  别唧唧喳喳
That's enough, chatterboxes.

161
00:10:48,668 --> 00:10:51,566
快吃早餐
Finish up your breakfasts.

162
00:10:51,604 --> 00:10:55,131
你也会走吗?
Are you going to leave us, too?

163
00:10:55,174 --> 00:10:57,507
当然不会
Of course not!

164
00:10:58,144 --> 00:11:00,341
我为什么要走?
Why should I leave you?

165
00:11:00,380 --> 00:11:02,610
他们也说不会
The others said they wouldn't

166
00:11:02,649 --> 00:11:04,480
但还是走了  出事了
but they did, and then it happened.

167
00:11:04,550 --> 00:11:06,518
别乱说!
Be quiet!

168
00:11:08,121 --> 00:11:09,748
什么意思?
What do you mean, Anne?

169
00:11:09,822 --> 00:11:12,950
出什么事了?
What happened?

170
00:11:12,992 --> 00:11:17,258
妈妈变疯了
Mummy went mad.

171
00:11:17,297 --> 00:11:20,061
-没事  -有事
-Nothing happened.  -Yes, it did.

172
00:11:20,099 --> 00:11:22,067
-不  没事!  -有事的!
-No, it didn't!  -Yes, it did!

173
00:11:22,101 --> 00:11:24,228
不要吵
Be quiet.

174
00:11:26,139 --> 00:11:29,108
怎么回事?  我要你们
What's going on? I want those plates empty

175
00:11:29,142 --> 00:11:31,474
一分钟内吃完  听到吗?
in less than a minute. Is that clear?

176
00:11:34,814 --> 00:11:37,044
米尔丝太太  能出来一会吗?
Mrs. Mills, would you come outside a moment?

177
00:11:37,083 --> 00:11:39,142
我有话和你说
I'd like a word with you.

178
00:11:40,920 --> 00:11:42,387
是的  太太
Yes, ma'am.

179
00:11:46,059 --> 00:11:48,991
邮差每逢星期三来收信
The postman usually comes every Wednesday.

180
00:11:50,330 --> 00:11:51,497
但我刚看了邮箱
But I just checked the letterbox

181
00:11:51,497 --> 00:11:52,929
这星期他没来过
and this week he hasn't.

182
00:11:54,167 --> 00:11:56,101
我不太明白太太的意思
I'm afraid I don't follow, ma'am.

183
00:11:56,135 --> 00:11:58,126
这封信件应该
This letter should have been collected

184
00:11:58,171 --> 00:12:00,731
在五天前送到报馆
and delivered to the newspaper five days ago.

185
00:12:00,773 --> 00:12:02,240
就是聘佣广告
It's an advertisement for servants.

186
00:12:02,275 --> 00:12:03,469
它没有刊登
Since it was never published

187
00:12:03,509 --> 00:12:06,307
你们怎么会上门的?
would you explain what you're doing here?

188
00:12:06,346 --> 00:12:08,847
噢  明白了
Oh, I understand.

189
00:12:09,082 --> 00:12:12,076
太太  那就是你开门时
Ma'am, that's what I was going to say to you

190
00:12:12,076 --> 00:12:13,942
我想解释的
when you opened the door to us.

191
00:12:14,020 --> 00:12:16,511
事实上我们只是路过
The truth is that we just come by

192
00:12:16,589 --> 00:12:18,853
碰碰运气
