00:36:14,481 --> 00:36:16,024
分明是说话声
There were voices. I'm telling you.

578
00:36:16,061 --> 00:36:18,889
-妈妈  你看  -有男孩和两个女人在说话
-Mummy, look!  -A boy and two women, talking together.

579
00:36:18,889 --> 00:36:20,823
妈妈  你看
Mummy, look!

580
00:36:22,534 --> 00:36:24,593
我昨天画的
I did it yesterday.

581
00:36:24,636 --> 00:36:26,331
这是父亲  母亲
This is the father, this is the mother,

582
00:36:26,371 --> 00:36:29,738
维克多  还有老妇人
this is Victor, and this is the old woman.

583
00:36:29,775 --> 00:36:31,675
这些数字是什么意思?
What do these numbers stand for?

584
00:36:31,710 --> 00:36:33,940
是我看见他们的次数
That's the number of times I've seen them.

585
00:36:33,979 --> 00:36:36,447
老妇人最常见
I've seen the old woman the most.

586
00:36:40,886 --> 00:36:42,786
噢  我的天
Oh, God in Heaven.

587
00:36:42,821 --> 00:36:44,820
米尔丝太太  去叫特德先生  告诉他
Mrs. Mills, go and call Mr. Tuttle. Tell him

588
00:36:44,820 --> 00:36:46,690
我们要立刻搜屋
we have to search the whole house immediately

589
00:36:46,725 --> 00:36:47,692
天黑前必须搜清楚
before it gets dark.

590
00:36:47,759 --> 00:36:50,057
-是的  太太  这就去  -妈咪!
-Yes, ma'am. There, now.  -Mummy!

591
00:36:50,095 --> 00:36:51,357
宝贝  别怕
Yes, darling. It's all right.

592
00:36:51,396 --> 00:36:54,661
妈妈会保护你们
Nothing will happen to you while Mummy's here.

593
00:36:54,699 --> 00:36:57,930
妈妈  我真的好害怕
Look, Mummy, She really scares me.

594
00:36:57,969 --> 00:36:59,027
看起来她没在看你
It's as if she's not looking at you,

595
00:36:59,070 --> 00:37:00,594
其实她盯着你
but she can see you.

596
00:37:00,639 --> 00:37:03,574
整天都在说  "跟我来"
And she's always around saying "Come with me".

597
00:37:03,608 --> 00:37:05,371
安  别对我说谎
No, Anne, don't lie to me.

598
00:37:05,410 --> 00:37:08,072
我没说谎  她还问这问那
Honestly, Mummy, and she asks me things.

599
00:37:08,113 --> 00:37:10,104
维克多说她是巫婆
Victor told me she's a witch.

600
00:37:10,148 --> 00:37:11,513
问你什么?
What does she ask you?

601
00:37:11,583 --> 00:37:13,517
什么都问
Things.

602
00:37:15,153 --> 00:37:18,281
她呼吸散发臭味
Her breath smells.

603
00:37:21,159 --> 00:37:23,654
必须拉开所有窗帘
We have to open all the curtains.

604
00:37:23,654 --> 00:37:26,061
搜遍每一个昏暗角落
I don't want any dark corners where someone could hide.

605
00:37:26,061 --> 00:37:27,094
是的  太太
Yes, ma'am.

606
00:37:27,132 --> 00:37:28,190
你们两个搜右面
You both search the right side

607
00:37:28,233 --> 00:37:29,530
我搜左面
and I'll take the left.

608
00:37:29,568 --> 00:37:31,433
然后上楼搜
Then we'll search upstairs.

609
00:38:42,574 --> 00:38:44,474
也许他们是鬼
Perhaps they're ghosts

610
00:38:44,509 --> 00:38:46,670
从前就住在这屋子
who lived in this house before.

611
00:38:46,711 --> 00:38:49,339
别犯傻  告诉过你
Don't be stupid. I've already told you.

612
00:38:49,380 --> 00:38:50,847
鬼披着白布
Ghosts go about in white sheets

613
00:38:50,882 --> 00:38:53,612
戴着锁链  并且发出呜呜的声音
and carry chains and go "Ooo".

614
00:38:53,685 --> 00:38:54,947
安
Now, Anne.

615
00:38:55,019 --> 00:38:57,544
你为什么胡编故事?
Why do you make up such stories?

616
00:38:57,622 --> 00:38:59,647
不是编的  书上写的
I don't. I read them in books.

617
00:38:59,724 --> 00:39:01,589
你不可全信
Well, you shouldn't believe everything

618
00:39:01,626 --> 00:39:02,888
书上写的东西
that you read in books.

619
00:39:02,927 --> 00:39:04,417
妈妈也这么说
That's what our mother says.

620
00:39:04,462 --> 00:39:08,057
她说鬼故事都是垃圾
She says all this stuff about ghosts is rubbish

621
00:39:08,099 --> 00:39:10,033
她要我们
and then she expects us

622
00:39:10,068 --> 00:39:12,298
相信圣经里写的东西
to believe everything written in the Bible.

623
00:39:12,337 --> 00:39:13,827
你信不信?
And don't you believe it?

624
00:39:13,872 --> 00:39:15,032
不可不信
I believe some things.

625
00:39:15,073 --> 00:39:17,439
但不可全信  比如不信
But, for example, I don't believe

626
00:39:17,475 --> 00:39:20,069
上帝七天创造了世界
that God made the world in seven days.

627
00:39:20,111 --> 00:39:21,772
也不信诺亚方舟
And I don't believe that Noah

628
00:39:21,813 --> 00:39:24,043
能装载全部的动物
got all those animals into one boat

629
00:39:24,082 --> 00:39:26,676
不信圣灵是鸽子
or the Holy Spirit is a dove.

630
00:39:26,751 --> 00:39:29,015
对  我也不信
No, I don't believe that, either.

631
00:39:29,087 --> 00:39:30,782
鸽子根本不神圣
Doves are anything but holy.

632
00:39:30,855 --> 00:39:32,713
它们在窗台拉屎
They poo on our windows.

633
00:39:38,196 --> 00:39:42,193
和你妈妈说过这些吗?
Have you mentioned any of this to your mother?

634
00:39:46,004 --> 00:39:47,665
哦
Oh.

635
00:40:47,565 --> 00:40:49,531
太太
Ma'am.

636
00:40:49,967 --> 00:40:51,228
什么事?
Yes?

637
00:40:51,669 --> 00:40:53,567
到处都搜过了  太太
They've searched everywhere, ma'am.

638
00:40:53,605 --> 00:40:55,095
没有人
There's no one.

639
00:40:55,139 --> 00:40:56,970
知道了
I see.

640
00:40:58,943 --> 00:41:01,741
米尔丝太太
Mrs. Mills.

641
00:41:01,779 --> 00:41:03,337
是的  太太
Yes, ma'am?

642
00:41:03,381 --> 00:41:06,282
你对这个有何见解?
Do you have any idea what this might be?

643
00:41:08,253 --> 00:41:10,221
是本相册  太太
This is a photograph album, ma'am.

644
00:41:10,255 --> 00:41:11,745
看  他们都睡着了
No, but look. They're all asleep.

645
00:41:11,823 --> 00:41:13,848
看
Look.

646
00:41:13,925 --> 00:41:16,621
他们不是在睡觉  是死了
They're not asleep, ma'am. They're dead.

647
00:41:18,363 --> 00:41:20,125
这是本遗照相册
This is a book of the dead.

648
00:41:20,164 --> 00:41:22,064
在上个世纪
In the last century, I believe

649
00:41:22,100 --> 00:41:24,000
人死后通常被拍成遗照
they used to take photographs of the dead

650
00:41:24,035 --> 00:41:25,935
以期待他们的灵魂
in the hopes that their souls

651
00:41:25,970 --> 00:41:28,803
能得以续存于世
would go on living through the portraits.

652
00:41:31,609 --> 00:41:33,907
甚至有集体照
There are even group portraits.

653
00:41:33,945 --> 00:41:36,937
还有小孩
And children!

654
00:41:36,981 --> 00:41:39,779
噢  太可怕了
Oh, it's macabre!

655
00:41:41,519 --> 00:41:44,147
怎么会如此迷信?
How could these people be so superstitious?

656
00:41:44,222 --> 00:41:46,588
失去亲人的悲情
Grief over the death of a loved one

657
00:41:46,624 --> 00:41:50,754
会令人做出不可思议的事
can lead people to do the strangest things.

658
00:41:54,032 --> 00:41:57,160
扔掉它  别留在屋里
Get rid of it, I don't want it in the house.

659
00:41:57,201 --> 00:41:59,066
是的  太太
Yes, ma'am

660
00:42:11,214 --> 00:42:12,283
米尔丝太太  这里很冷
Mrs. Mills, it's cold.

661
00:42:12,283 --> 00:42:14,474
何不坐过来取暖?
Why don't you come and sit by the fire?

662
00:42:26,497 --> 00:42:29,128
太谢谢了  太太
Thank you very much, ma'am.

663
00:42:29,167 --> 00:42:33,126
说说你以前在这里干活的事
So tell me about when you worked here before.

664
00:42:33,171 --> 00:42:35,306
也要照看小孩吗?
Did you have to look after children then?

665
00:42:35,306 --> 00:42:39,834
不  我只负责管家
No, I was in charge of organizing the housework.

666
00:42:39,877 --> 00:42:42,737
嗯  有很多佣人吗?
Hmm. Were there many servants?

667
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:45,512
大概有十五个
Oh, about fifteen.

668
00:42:46,784 --> 00:42:47,676
不过最后
Though in the end

669
00:42:47,676 --> 00:42:50,113
只剩下我们三个
there were just the three of us left.

670
00:42:50,188 --> 00:42:51,519
为什么?
Why?

671
00:42:51,556 --> 00:42:53,820
主人搬到伦敦去了
My employers moved to London.

672
00:42:53,858 --> 00:42:57,817
他们渐渐就不常来了
They came here less and less,

673
00:42:57,862 --> 00:42:59,955
没了以前那么热闹
it being so out of the way like.

674
00:42:59,998 --> 00:43:04,067
屋子就这样被空置了
So gradually the house just became empty.

675
00:43:05,202 --> 00:43:08,037
大家最终都离开这个岛
Everybody ends up leaving this damned island.

676
00:43:09,973 --> 00:43:12,572
1940年夏  我家人也走了
My family left in the summer of 1940

677
00:43:12,610 --> 00:43:14,546
就在沦陷之前
just before the invasion.

678
00:43:16,780 --> 00:43:18,310
此后再也没有音讯
That was the last I've heard of them.

679
00:43:20,351 --> 00:43:21,875
噢
Ohh.

680
00:43:23,054 --> 00:43:25,716
我不责怪他们
I don't blame them.

681
00:43:25,790 --> 00:43:29,351
其实我们也走了
Actually, we left, too.

682
00:43:29,394 --> 00:43:31,089
但你知道
Although, you know,

683
00:43:31,129 --> 00:43:33,256
有时即使是人走了
sometimes when you leave a place

684
00:43:33,297 --> 00:43:37,791
心还是一直在
it's like it's there with you all the time.

685
00:43:37,835 --> 00:43:41,566
我总觉得从未离开过这间屋
I always felt like I never left this house.

686
00:43:41,606 --> 00:43:42,836
你为什么要走?
Why did you leave?

687
00:43:43,875 --> 00:43:46,207
是因为肺结核肆虐
Oh, it was on account of the tuberculosis.

688
00:43:46,244 --> 00:43:49,475
全区都被疏散了
The whole area was evacuated.

689
00:43:49,514 --> 00:43:51,982
噢
Ohh.

690
00:43:52,016 --> 00:43:54,177
丽蒂亚因此变成哑巴了?
Was that when Lydia went dumb?

691
00:43:54,252 --> 00:43:57,244
我想是的
Yes, I think so

692
00:43:57,321 --> 00:44:01,155
不过近来我的记性不太好
though my memory's a bit rusty these days, ma'am.

693
00:44:01,192 --> 00:44:02,819
她发生什么事了?
What happened to her?

694
00:44:08,166 --> 00:44:11,158
有一天她突然
It was suddenly one day,

695
00:44:11,202 --> 00:44:15,161
不再说话了
she just stopped talking.

696
00:44:15,206 --> 00:44:18,403
必定有原因
There must've been a reason.

697
00:44:18,443 --> 00:44:20,707
不会莫名其妙变哑巴
People don't just stop talking.

698
00:44:20,745 --> 00:44:22,269
一定是受到什么
These things are always the result

699
00:44:22,313 --> 00:44:25,476
精神刺激之类的事
of some sort of trauma.

700
00:44:25,516 --> 00:44:27,609
肯定发生了一些事
Something must've happened to her.

701
00:44:31,923 --> 00:44:33,618
主人对你们好吗?
Did your employers treat you well?

702
00:44:33,658 --> 00:44:35,626
他们对我们很好
Oh, they were always very kind to us.

703
00:44:35,660 --> 00:44:38,720
视我们如同一家人
They treated us just like family.

704
00:44:41,032 --> 00:44:44,031
太太  我该去休息了
You know, ma'am, I think I will go to bed.

705
00:44:44,031 --> 00:44:47,132
否则明天不能早起
I'll never be able to get up in the morning.

706
00:44:47,171 --> 00:44:48,729
去吧
Off you go.

707
00:44:48,773 --> 00:44:50,638
我想一个人再坐会儿
I'm going to stay here a while longer.

708
00:44:50,675 --> 00:44:52,472
好  太太
Yes, ma'am.

709
00:45:26,511 --> 00:45:30,174
妈妈对你太严格了
I'm sorry I was so hard on you.

710
00:45:36,420 --> 00:45:38,888
原谅妈妈好吗?
Can you forgive me?

711
00:45:44,529 --> 00:45:46,121
安
Anne.

712
00:46:05,149 --> 00:46:06,343
妈咪
Mummy.

713
00:46:06,417 --> 00:46:07,475
怎么了?
What?

714
00:46:07,552 --> 00:46:09,986
爸爸几时回来?
When's Daddy coming home?

715
00:46:10,021 --> 00:46:13,115
打完仗就回来
When the war's over.

716
00:46:13,191 --> 00:46:15,751
他为什么去打仗?
Why did he go to war?

717
00:46:15,793 --> 00:46:19,957
没有人欺负我们的
I mean, nobody's done anything bad to us.

718
00:46:19,997 --> 00:46:22,124
爸爸去...
Daddy went...

719
00:46:24,835 --> 00:46:28,703
是因为他很勇敢
Daddy went because he's very brave

720
00:46:28,739 --> 00:46:31,264
因为他不愿意
and because he wasn't prepared

721
00:46:31,309 --> 00:46:34,642
屈服听从德国人
to let the Germans tell him what he had to do.

722
00:46:34,679 --> 00:46:36,374
为什么?
Why?

723
00:46:44,288 --> 00:46:47,621
查尔斯
Charles,

724
00:46:47,658 --> 00:46:49,626
你在哪里?
where are you?

725
00:49:37,461 --> 00:49:40,362
米尔丝太太!
Mrs. Mills!

726
00:49:40,398 --> 00:49:42,263
米尔丝太太!
Mrs. Mills!

727
00:49:43,534 --> 00:49:45,058
什么事?  太太
What's the matter, ma'am?

728
00:49:45,102 --> 00:49:47,696
快给我音乐室的锁匙
The key to the music room, give it to me!

729
00:49:47,738 --> 00:49:48,705
快点!
Quickly!

730
00:49:48,739 --> 00:49:49,706
怎么了?
What's happening, ma'am?

731
00:49:49,740 --> 00:49:51,367
快点!
Come on!

732
00:50:00,184 --> 00:50:02,675
噢  天哪
Oh, my God.

733
00:50:02,753 --> 00:50:04,550
噢!
Ohh!

734
00:50:04,588 --> 00:50:07,557
我亲自查过房间
I checked that room myself.

735
00:50:09,627 --> 00:50:11,561
里面没有人
It was empty.

736
00:50:11,595 --> 00:50:13,862
吃点药片  太太
Take these tablets, ma'am.

737
00:50:13,862 --> 00:50:15,664
-但...  -对你身体有益
-And yet...  -They'll do you good.

738
00:50:15,664 --> 00:50:18,603
我感到那里确实有人
I felt as if there was someone else there.

739
00:50:20,103 --> 00:50:22,869
不是人类
And it wasn't human.

740
00:50:23,407 --> 00:50:26,638
屋里有东西
There is something in this house.

741
00:50:26,677 --> 00:50:28,577
不祥之物
Something diabolic.

742
00:50:28,612 --> 00:50:30,102
太太
Ma'am.

743
00:50:30,147 --> 00:50:33,139
那是尚未...
Something which is not...

744
00:50:34,952 --> 00:50:37,648
尚未得到安息的冤魂
not at rest.

745
00:50:40,891 --> 00:50:43,553
我知道你不相信
I know you don't believe it.

746
00:50:43,594 --> 00:50:46,222
你不信的  对吗?
You don't believe it, do you?

747
00:50:46,263 --> 00:50:47,696
我不责怪你
I don't blame you.

748
00:50:47,731 --> 00:50:51,827
以前我也不信
I used to not believe these things.

749
00:50:53,037 --> 00:50:56,632
我相信  太太
I do believe it, ma'am.

750
00:50:58,108 --> 00:51:01,271
我一直都相信这些事
I've always believed in those things.

751
00:51:01,312 --> 00:51:03,576
虽然难以说清
They're not easy to explain,

752
00:51:03,614 --> 00:51:05,445
但确实存在
but they do happen.

753
00:51:05,483 --> 00:51:10,284
幽灵的故事
We've all heard stories of the beyond

754
00:51:10,354 --> 00:51:12,448
我们时有所闻
now and then,

755
00:51:13,524 --> 00:51:20,521
我想有时阴界
and I think sometimes the world of the dead

756
00:51:20,564 --> 00:51:24,295
会和阳界交错在一起
gets mixed up with the world of the living.

757
00:51:25,935 --> 00:51:27,395
这不可能
But it's impossible.

758
00:51:27,438 --> 00:51:29,838
上帝绝不允许这种异事
The Lord would never allow such an aberration.

759
00:51:29,874 --> 00:51:30,932
活人和死人
The living and the dead

760
00:51:30,975 --> 00:51:35,071
只有在终世审判时才相会
will only meet at the end of eternity.

761
00:51:36,112 --> 00:51:37,842
圣经是这么写的
It says so in the Bible.

762
00:51:37,882 --> 00:51:40,373
太太
Ma'am,

763
00:51:40,451 --> 00:51:45,252
不是所有事都有合理解释
there isn't always an answer for everything.

764
00:51:56,600 --> 00:51:58,329
太太您要上哪里?
Where are you off to, ma'am?

765
00:51:58,369 --> 00:52:01,167
我要去村庄拜访迈格拉神父
I'm going to the village to pay Father McGraw a visit.

766
00:52:01,205 --> 00:52:03,435
他不愿来  我就上门
If he won't come here, then I shall go to him.

767
00:52:03,474 --> 00:52:04,668
我要带他来这里
I shall bring him back.

768
00:52:04,708 --> 00:52:06,235
太太您应该等天气变好
Ma'am, you should wait till the weather improves.

769
00:52:06,235 --> 00:52:08,674
我等得太久了
I've waited long enough.

770
00:52:08,712 --> 00:52:11,342
太太  神父告诉我...
Ma'am, the priest told me that...

771
00:52:11,342 --> 00:52:13,142
我不管他告诉你什么
I don't care what he told you!

772
00:52:13,217 --> 00:52:15,310
我要他亲自告诉我
I want him to tell me personally!

773
00:52:15,386 --> 00:52:16,944
他今天一定得来
He must come today!

774
00:52:17,021 --> 00:52:18,818
那你打算怎么说?
But what are you going to tell him?

775
00:52:18,856 --> 00:52:21,620
